<!--
VOICING PLAN — Go To Dark Gethsemane (Eb major)
================================================

PHRASE 1 (mm. 1-4): Sparse, solemn opening
- m1: I "334" (Eb Bb Eb G) in LH — open, grounded; RH "33" Eb G ascending
- m2: VIm–I alternation. LH stays in C3 range on VI (C G C), drops to Eb2 on I
- m3: Four-chord progression with smooth inner voice motion (G–Eb–D in LH inner)
- m4: VIm7 with 4-note LH (C G Eb Bb) — rich half-diminished sound; V three-note RH

PHRASE 2 (mm. 5-8): Rising chromatic tension
- m5: I–VIm–V–I repeated; LH stays close, RH rises from Eb4 to Bb4
- m6: Chromatic VI (C major with E-natural) and VIIø7 (D F Ab) — darkest moment
  Voice leading: E-natural → D (half step) in RH is the key chromatic move
- m7: IIIm substituted for non-diatonic G major; smooth bass descent G–Bb–F–C
- m8: Final II→V half cadence; LH full four-note V chord at cadence

PHRASE 3 (mm. 9-12): Return and cadence
- m9: I–IV–I; IV (Ab) used on chromatic passing moment from original
- m10: VI–I as before; LH now four notes on I (Eb Bb G Eb)
- m11: IV–I–IIm–I with full 4-note LH on I; maximum harmonic density
- m12: I–V–I final cadence; RH reaches 4 notes on final I; LH 5 notes final chord

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS
========================
- Bass line in phrases 1-2: Eb–C–Bb–C–Bb–G–Bb descending-then-rising
  follows the dark Gethsemane narrative arc
- Inner LH line: G3–Eb3–D3–G3 across mm. 1-4 creates a stepwise inner voice
- m6 chromatic: E-natural in RH (as written in lead sheet VI annotation) creates
  a moment of tension; LH has D F Ab (half-dim). Both resolve stepwise to I.
- m12 final chord: LH reaches 5 notes (Eb Bb Eb G Bb) — full sonority at close

TEXTURE ARC
===========
- mm. 1-4:  Sparse (2 RH, 3-4 LH). Solemn opening appropriate to text.
- mm. 5-8:  Building. RH adds third notes. Chromatic VI/VIIø7 peak in m6.
- mm. 9-12: Full texture returning. Final I chord in m12 has 4 RH + 5 LH.
            Root position throughout cadence — convergence and resolution.
-->
